-- Argos May Sell Up to 1 Trillion Pesos in Debt, Republica Says
-- B y   A n d r e a   J a r a m i l l o
-- 2012-01-19T13:35:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-19/argos-may-sell-up-to-1-trillion-pesos-in-debt-republica-says.html
Cementos Argos SA (CEMARGOS) ,  Colombia ’s
biggest cement maker, is seeking approval from authorities to
sell as much as 1 trillion pesos ($549 million) in bonds and
short-term notes in the local market, La Republica newspaper
said, citing a report from the financial regulator.  A call to the company’s press office by Bloomberg News
wasn’t immediately returned.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrea Jaramillo in Bogota at 
 ajaramillo1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
